Temporary Configure Static IP Address in Linux

# ip addr add 172.19.1.10/24 dev eth2

Remove all ips from interface
# ip addr flush eth2


Display All Network Interfaces
$ ip link show
$ ip link show eth2
$ ip addr show
$ ip addr
$ ip --color addr show eth2

JSON
$ ip -j -p addr show eth2


Enable the Network Interface
# ip link set eth2 up
# ip link set eth2 down

DHCP
# dhclient -r
# dhclient

Virtual network interfaces on Linux
# modprobe dummy
# ip link add eth0 type dummy
# ip link show eth0
# ifconfig eth0 hw ether C8:D7:4A:4E:47:50
# ip addr add 192.168.1.100/24 brd + dev eth0 label eth0:0
# ip link set dev eth0 up
# ip a


# ip addr del 192.168.1.100/24 brd + dev eth0 label eth0:0
# sudo ip link delete eth0 type dummy
# rmmod dummy
